This paper is about neural dialogue modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the use of neural networks for dialogue modeling, which is a subfield of NLP known as "Computational Linguistics" (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel approach for conversation-level inference, which involves running beam search across multiple conversation turns, and this approach falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Neural Networks" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach using the Persona-Chat dataset, which is a dataset for dialogue modeling, and this falls under the category of "Software Development" (cs.SD) as it involves the creation and use of software tools for NLP tasks.
